text: error correction :  if you are getting error like [cannot center sparse matrices: pass ''with_mean = False' instead] even after writing same code . Then try writing StandardScaler(with_mean = False) instead of StandardScaler()

author: @DJ-jf4qg
text: ALERT: replace all StandardScaler() with StandardScaler(with_mean=False) The reason that adding with_mean=False resolved my error is that the StandardScaler is subtracting the mean from each feature, which can result in some features having negative values. However, StandardScaler() alone assumes that the features have positive values, which can cause issues when working with features that have negative values. By setting with_mean=False, the StandardScaler does not subtract the mean from each feature, and instead scales the features based on their variance. This can help preserve the positive values of the features and avoid issues.
